    This version refines the nonlinear harmonic oscillator acceleration model by:
    - Including all relevant polynomial terms up to cubic order in position (x0) and velocity (x1).
    - Capturing nonlinear stiffness (Duffing-type) and nonlinear damping effects.
    - Adding cross terms that represent coupling between position and velocity.
    - Explicitly enforcing physically meaningful signs for restoring force and damping terms by parameter transformations.

    Parameters:
    - x0 (np.ndarray): Position at time t
    - x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity at time t
