    - Linear stiffness and damping terms
    - Quadratic, cubic, and quartic nonlinearities in position (x0)
    - Quadratic and cubic nonlinearities in velocity (x1)
    - Cross terms coupling position and velocity at various orders
    - Mixed nonlinear coupling terms to capture complex interactions

    Physically:
    - params[1]*x0 models linear restoring force (-k*x)
    - params[2]*x1 models linear damping (-c*v)
    - Higher order powers of x0 model anharmonic stiffness effects (Duffing-type nonlinearity)
    - Higher order powers of x1 model nonlinear damping or drag effects
    - Cross and mixed terms capture coupling between position and velocity dynamics

    Parameters:
        x0 (np.ndarray): Position at time t
        x1 (np.ndarray): Velocity at time t
        params (np.ndarray): Array of 12 coefficients

            params[0]: constant offset / external force bias term
